-- Egypt Allocates $270 Million for Sinai Development: MENA
-- B y   S a l m a   E l   W a r d a n y
-- 2012-09-03T14:12:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-03/egypt-allocates-270-million-for-sinai-development-mena.html
Egypt’s government allocated 1.65
billion pounds ($270 million) for development and infrastructure
projects in the  Sinai Peninsula , the state-run Middle East News
Agency reported today.  The government is considering establishing three free-trade
zones in Rafah and Arish in north Sinai and Nuweiba in south
Sinai, Cairo-based MENA reported, citing the head of the Sinai
Development Authority.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Salma El Wardany in Cairo at 
 selwardany@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  